SIMPLE: impalpable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impalpable
<hw>Im*pal"pa*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>palpable</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>impalpable</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not palpable; that cannot
be felt; extremely fine, so that no grit can be perceived by
touch.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Impalpable</xex> powder.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not material; intangible; incorporeal.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Impalpable</xex>, void, and bodiless.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not apprehensible, or readily apprehensible, by the
mind; unreal; <as>as, <ex>impalpable</ex> distinctions</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impalpably</ent>⟦br⟧
